{"title_page": "Feralpisal\u00f2", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Feralpisal\u00f2\n| image = Feralpisal\u00f2.png\n| image_size = 250px\n| fullname = Feralpisal\u00f2 Srl\n| nickname = ''I Leoni del Garda'' (The Lions of [[Garda Lake]]), ''Verdazzurri'' (The Green and Lightblues), ''Verdebl\u00f9'' (The Green and Blues), ''Gardesani'' or ''Benacensi'' (People from [[Garda Lake]])\n| founded  = 2009\n| ground = [[Stadio Lino Turina]],<br />[[Sal\u00f2]], Italy\n| capacity = 2,364.\n| chairman = Giuseppe Pasini\n| manager = Stefano Sottili\n| league = {{Italian football updater|Feralpisalo}}\n| season = {{Italian football updater|Feralpisalo2}}\n| position = {{Italian football updater|Feralpisalo3}}\n| website =https://www.feralpisalo.it/\n|pattern_b1 = _feralpi1920h\n|body1 = 0000FF\n|pattern_la1 = \n|leftarm1 = 0000FF\n|pattern_ra1 = \n|rightarm1 = 0000FF\n|pattern_sh1 = \n|shorts1 = 0000FF\n|socks1 = 0000FF\n|pattern_b2 = _feralpi1920a\n|body2 = FFFFFF\n|pattern_la2 = _lightblueborder\n|leftarm2 = FFFFFF\n|pattern_ra2 = _lightblueborder\n|rightarm2 = FFFFFF\n|shorts2 = FFFFFF\n|pattern_sh2 = \n|socks2 = FFFFFF\n|body3 = 000000\n|pattern_b3 = _feralpi1920t\n|leftarm3 = 000000\n|pattern_la3 = _whiteborder\n|rightarm3 = 000000\n|pattern_ra3 = _whiteborder\n|shorts3 = 000000\n|socks3 = 000000\n}}\n\n[[File:Stadio Lino Turina.JPG|thumb|right|Stadio ''Lino Turina'']]\n\n'''Feralpisal\u00f2''' is an [[Football in Italy|Italian association football]] club located in [[Sal\u00f2]], [[Lombardy]], and representing also the nearby town of [[Lonato del Garda]], Lombardy.\n\nThe club currently play in [[Serie C]], the third tier of Italian football.\n\n==History==\nThe club was founded in summer 2009, from the merger between two clubs, both of [[Serie D]]:\n* '''[[A.C. Sal\u00f2]]''' of [[Sal\u00f2]], founded in 1985, as ''A.C. Sal\u00f2 Benaco'' and so renamed since 2001,\n* '''[[A.C. Feralpi Lonato]]''' of [[Lonato del Garda]], founded in 1980, as ''A.C. Lonato'' and so renamed since 1985.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bresciaoggi.it/stories/Sport/59325__feralpi-sal__ununione_gigante/|title=Feralpi-Sal\u00f2, \u00e8 un'unione gigante|first=Edizioni Brescia|last=S.p.A.|publisher=|accessdate=17 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 August 2009 the club was admitted to [[Lega Pro Seconda Divisione]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.feralpisalo.it/stampa09/gbs12ago2009.pdf|title=FERALPISAL\u00d2|website=www.feralpisalo.it|accessdate=17 September 2018}}{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> in place of not admitted [[U.S. Pistoiese 1921|Pistoiese]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bresciaoggi.it/stories/Home/76166_macalli_il_sal__ripescato_in_seconda_divisione/|title=Bresciaoggi|first=Edizioni Brescia|last=S.p.A.|website=Bresciaoggi.it|accessdate=17 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923194723/http://www.bresciaoggi.it/stories/Home/76166_macalli_il_sal__ripescato_in_seconda_divisione/|archive-date=23 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bresciaoggi.it/stories/Sport/77408__feralpi_sal_una_scalata_da_vertigine/|title=Feralpi Sal\u00f2, una scalata da vertigine|first=Edizioni Brescia|last=S.p.A.|publisher=|accessdate=17 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn the season 2010\u201311 from [[Lega Pro Seconda Divisione]] group A,  the club gained  promotion to [[Lega Pro Prima Divisione]] via the playoffs, for the first time ever.\n\n==Colours and badge==\n\nIts colours are [[blue]] and [[green]]: representing ''[[A.C. Sal\u00f2 Valsabbia|Sal\u00f2]]'' and ''[[A.C. Feralpi Lonato|Feralpi Lonato]]''.<ref>http://miticosalo.altervista.org//stampa09/bsoggi13giu2009.pdf</ref>\n\n==Current squad==\n''As of 31 January 2020.''\n\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player | no=  1 | nat= ITA | name= [[Luca Liverani]] |pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player | no=  3 | nat= ITA | name= [[Davide Mordini]]| pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player | no=  4 | nat= ITA | name= [[Nico