1306)</small><br />[[Democratic Party (Cook Islands)|Democratic Party]]<br><small>(2006\u20132010)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Cook Islands Party/meta/color}}; color:white\"| 9\n| [[Henry Puna]]<br>{{small|(1949\u2013)}}\n| 30 November 2010\n| Incumbent\n| [[Cook Islands Party]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Cook Islands]]\n**[[Politics of the Cook Islands]]\n**[[Monarchy in the Cook Islands]]\n***[[Queen's Representative]]\n*[[Lists of incumbents]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Cook_Islands.html World Statesmen \u2013 Cook Islands]\n\n{{CookIsPMs}}\n{{Cook Islands topics}}\n{{Heads of state and government of Oceania}}\n{{Prime Minister}}\n\n[[Category:Politics of the Cook Islands]]\n[[Category:Government of the Cook Islands]]\n[[Category:Lists of prime ministers by country|Cook Islands, List of Prime Ministers of]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of the Cook Islands| ]]\n[[Category:Cook Islands-related lists|Prime Ministers]]\n", "text_old": "{{use New Zealand English|date=August 2019}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{short description|Cook Islands' head of government}}\n{{Infobox Political post\n|post            = Prime Minister\n|body            = the<br />Cook Islands\n|insignia        = Flag of the Cook Islands.svg\n|insigniasize    = 125px\n|insigniacaption = Flag of the Cook Islands\n|termlength      = \n|image           = Henry Puna 2015.jpg\n|imagesize       = 150px \n|incumbent       = [[Henry Puna]]\n|incumbentsince  = 30 November 2010\n|appointer       = \n|formation       = 4 August 1965\n|inaugural       = [[Albert Henry (politician)|Albert Henry]]\n|website         = \n}}\n{{Politics of the Cook Islands}}\n                               \nThe '''Prime Minister of the Cook Islands''' is the [[head of government]] of the [[Cook Islands]], a self-governing territory in [[Associated state|free association]] with [[New Zealand]]. The office was established in 1965, when [[History of the