ns]] (France), [[James Wynne]] (France)\n\n[[Lewis Brown (rugby league)|Lewis Brown]] (New Zealand), [[Greg Eastwood]] (New Zealand), [[Kalifa Faifai Loa]] (New Zealand), [[Kieran Foran]] (New Zealand), [[Issac Luke]] (New Zealand), [[Kevin Locke (rugby league)|Kevin Locke]], [[Simon Mannering]] (New Zealand), [[Ben Matulino]] (New Zealand), [[Kevin Proctor]] (New Zealand), [[Dean Whare]] (New Zealand), [[Solomone Kata]] (New Zealand)\n\n[[Macali Aizue]] (Papua New Guinea), [[Glen Nami]] (Papua New Guinea)\n\n[[David Fa'alogo]] (Samoa), [[Joseph Leilua]] (Samoa), [[Isaac Liu]] (Samoa), [[Tautau Moga]] (Samoa), [[Ben Roberts (rugby league)|Ben Roberts]] (Samoa), [[Tim Simona]] (Samoa), [[Antonio Winterstein]] (Samoa)\n\n[[Jordan James]] (Wales), [[Rhys Williams (rugby league)|Rhys Williams]] (Wales)\n\n[[Ryan Brierley]] (Scotland), [[Ben Kavanagh]] (Scotland), [[Kane Linnett]] (Scotland), [[Matty Russell]] (Scotland), [[Dale Ferguson (rugby league)|Dale Ferguson]] (Scotland), [[Lewis Tierney]] (Scotland), [[Ben Hellewell]] (Scotland), [[Euan Aitken]] (Scotland)\n|}\n\n===Top pointscorers===\nThe five highest overall points-scorers are goal-kickers with [[Johnathan Thurston]] being top, having scored 126 points; 106 of these points have come from 53 goals.  The highest points-scorers who are not goal kickers are [[Jason Nightingale]] and [[Ryan Hall (rugby league)|Ryan Hall]] who have both scored 44 points from 11 tries and are the joint sixth highest points scorers.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\" | '''Overall Four Nations Tournament Top Point-Scorers'''\n|-\n!width=20 abbr=\"Position\" |\n!width=150 |Player\n!width=150 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Tries\" |T\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals\" |G\n!width=20 abbr=\"Field goals\" |FG\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|-\n|1||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Johnathan Thurston]]\n|{{rl|Australia}}||5||53||0||'''126'''\n|-\n|2||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Cameron Smith]]\n|{{rl|Australia}}||4||